{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Ecclesiastes 10 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:1",
      "text": "Dying flies spoil the sweetness of the ointment. Wisdom and glory is more precious than a small and shortlived folly.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:2",
      "text": "The heart of a wise man is in his right hand, and the heart of a fool is in his left hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:3",
      "text": "Yea, and the fool when he walketh in the way, whereas he himself is a fool, esteemeth all men fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:4",
      "text": "If the spirit of him that hath power, ascend upon thee, leave not thy place: because care will make the greatest sins to cease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:5",
      "text": "There is an evil that I have seen under the sun, as it were by an error proceeding from the face of the prince:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:6",
      "text": "A fool set in high dignity, and the rich sitting beneath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:7",
      "text": "I have seen servants upon horses: and princes walking on the ground as servants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:8",
      "text": "He that diggeth a pit, shall fall into it: and he that breaketh a hedge, a serpent shall bite him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:9",
      "text": "He that removeth stones, shall be hurt by them: and he that cutteth trees, shall be wounded by them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:10",
      "text": "If the iron be blunt, and be not as before, but be made blunt, with much labour it shall be sharpened: and after industry shall follow wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:11",
      "text": "If a serpent bite in silence, he is nothing better that backbiteth secretly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:12",
      "text": "The words of the mouth of a wise man are grace: but the lips of a fool shall throw him down headlong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:13",
      "text": "The beginning of his words is folly, and the end of his talk is a mischievous error.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:14",
      "text": "A fool multiplieth words. A man cannot tell what hath been before him: and what shall be after him, who can tell him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:15",
      "text": "The labour of fools shall afflict them that know not how to go to the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:16",
      "text": "Woe to thee, O land, when thy king is a child, and when the princes eat in the morning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:17",
      "text": "Blessed is the land, whose king is noble, and whose princes eat in due season for refreshment, and not for riotousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:18",
      "text": "By slothfulness a building shall be brought down, and through the weakness of hands, the house shall drop through.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:19",
      "text": "For laughter they make bread, and wine that the living may feast: and all things obey money.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ecclesiastes.10.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:20",
      "text": "Detract not the king, no not in thy thought; and speak not evil of the rich man in thy private chamber: because even the birds of the air will carry thy voice, and he that hath wings will tell what thou hast said.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
